author: MarketWatch
title: Stocks open slightly higher ahead of consumer-confidence data
text: U.S. stocks opened higher Tuesday, recovering some of the previous session's steep losses, as investors awaited data on consumer confidence. The S&P 500 SPX, +0.66% rose 2 points, or 0.1%, to 1,886, while the Dow Jones Industrial Average DJIA, +0.42% advanced 29 points, or 0.2%, to 16,037. The Nasdaq Composite COMP, +0.78% rose 15 points, or 0.3%, to 4,558.
